<item>
            <title>[LU-14942] Flaw in LU-13569 prevents recovery pings in routed networks</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14942</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13569&quot; title=&quot;LNet Health should not recover interfaces indefinitely&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-13569&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-13569&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; relies on the lpni_last_alive update in lnet_parse() to determine eligibility for recovery pings. However, in a routed network the lpni_last_alive being updated will likely be for a router rather than the message originator.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
